\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.6 Parent-Child Linkage and Incident Suppression During Active Problem Investigations
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
When a formal Problem record has been opened under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 for an active failure condition,
 that Problem record becomes the Parent record for that condition.
 Duplicate troubleshooting of the same underlying failure by independent technicians wastes remediation resources and risks contaminating the Problem investigation.
 The following mechanic governs incidents received while a relevant Parent Problem investigation is active.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
If a technician receives a new incident work order whose symptoms match those of an active Parent Problem record,
 the technician shall:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\lang english
Set the work order status to In Progress in accordance with work order operational standards maintained in the System of Engagement
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\lang english
Link the work order to the Parent Problem record via the Related Issues field in the System of Engagement
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\lang english
Document in the work order notes that the incident has been identified as related to an active Problem investigation,
 identifying the Parent record by its Redmine issue number and providing a brief notation of the matching symptoms.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\lang english
Not attempt independent troubleshooting on the underlying failure condition while the Parent Problem investigation is active.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Related Issues link to the Parent Problem record is the required audit trail for why the child work order remains In Progress without independent resolution activity.
 This link shall be established before or concurrent with the In Progress status assignment.
 An In Progress work order with no Related Issues link to a Parent Problem record is not compliant with this section.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
At the time the Parent Problem record is resolved,
 the assigned technician shall revisit each linked child work order and close it with the appropriate terminal status in accordance with work order operational standards maintained in the System of Engagement
:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Duplicate
\series default
 if the Parent Problem resolution fully addressed the child work order's reported condition and no additional end-system work was required on the child work order's asset or user environment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Resolved
\series default
 if end-system work was required on the child work order's asset or user environment following or concurrent with the Problem resolution —
 for example,
 reinstalling software,
 restoring a user configuration,
 re-imaging a device,
 or performing any other technician action specific to the child work order's asset or user.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The closure rationale shall be documented in each child work order's notes at the time of closure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.7 Problem Record Spawn Triggers
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Two objective conditions automatically mandate that a formal Problem record be opened under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 The technician closing the qualifying incident work order shall evaluate whether either trigger has been met and shall open the Problem record if so.
 This obligation is not discretionary and is not satisfied by referencing the trigger threshold in the work order notes without opening the record.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Major Incident Trigger
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Every incident classified as Critical severity under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 without exception,
 shall generate a formal Problem record upon closure.
 The Problem record shall be opened no later than the close of business on the calendar day the incident work order is resolved.
 This requirement is non-negotiable.
 Critical severity incidents represent the most significant service failures within the Department's operational environment.
 The causes of those failures shall be formally investigated regardless of whether a technician believes the cause to be self-evident.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Recurring Incident Trigger
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Five (5) or more incidents against the same asset or service,
 within the same work order category,
 within any rolling thirty (30) calendar day window,
 shall automatically generate a formal Problem record.
 The technician closing the fifth qualifying incident shall open the Problem record at the time of that closure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
For purposes of this trigger:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The same-category requirement is essential.
 Five or more incidents across different categories on the same asset may indicate a heavily utilized or aging asset;
 five or more within the same category indicates a specific,
 repeating failure pattern in that functional dimension.
 Tickets in different categories do not aggregate toward this trigger,
 even if the total exceeds five.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The thirty (30) calendar day window is a rolling calculation,
 not a fixed calendar period.
 Any thirty-day span ending on the date of the most recent incident is the applicable window.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall monitor queue data to identify recurring incident patterns and shall notify the relevant technician if the threshold has been crossed without a corresponding Problem record.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Relationship to Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 Deprecated Asset Trigger
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Recurring Incident Trigger above shall not be conflated with the Deprecated Asset labor ceiling trigger defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 Section 6.5.
 These are related but distinct mechanisms.
 The 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 trigger uses a ninety (90) calendar day window to ask whether a Deprecated asset is failing with sufficient frequency to warrant accelerated replacement.
 The 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 trigger uses a thirty (30) calendar day window to ask whether something is actively wrong with an asset or service right now —
 a tighter window that reflects the need to investigate while evidence is fresh.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Both triggers may fire simultaneously on the same asset.
 When they do,
 the Problem investigation asks why the asset is failing while the disposition review asks whether it is worth fixing.
 These are complementary obligations,
 not conflicting ones,
 and both shall be executed.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
